Introduction

For this assignment, I picked randomly 4 countries’ top 100 apple music playlists by using a die. I tried to find the number of explicit songs in the playlists across 4 different countries. I compared them and tried to obtain a result because it would be interesting to see if countries worldwide all prefer explicit songs.

library(tidyverse)
library(rvest)

urls <- c("https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/top-100-australia/pl.18be1cf04dfd4ffb9b6b0453e8fae8f1",
          "https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/top-100-canada/pl.79bac9045a2540e0b195e983df8ba569",
          "https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/top-100-mexico/pl.df3f10ca27b1479087de2cd3f9f6716b",
          "https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/top-100-usa/pl.606afcbb70264d2eb2b51d8dbcfa6a12")


apple_data <- map_df(1:length(urls), function(i) {
  Sys.sleep(2)
  
  page <- read_html(urls[i])
  
  #Track Id
  trackId <- page %>% 
    html_elements(".songs-list") %>%
    html_elements("a") %>%
    html_attr("href") %>%
    .[str_detect(., "/song/")] %>%
    str_remove_all("https://music.apple.com/us/song/")
  
  #Title
  title <- page %>%
    html_elements(".songs-list-row__song-name") %>%
    html_text2()
  
  #Rank
  rank <- page %>%
    html_elements(".songs-list-row__rank") %>%
    html_text2()
  
  return(tibble(trackId, title, rank))
})

saveRDS(apple_data, "apple_data.rds")
library(tidyverse)
library(jsonlite)

apple_data <- readRDS("apple_data.rds")

trackIds <- apple_data$trackId %>%
  unique() %>%
  na.omit()

itunes_data <- map_df(1:length(trackIds), function(i) {
  Sys.sleep(2)
  song_id <- trackIds[i]
  url <- paste0("https://itunes.apple.com/lookup?id=", song_id)
  
  response <- fromJSON(url)
  data <- response$results
  
  return(tibble(data))
})

print(itunes_data)
saveRDS(itunes_data, "itunes_data.rds")
library(tidyverse)

apple_data <- readRDS("apple_data.rds")
itunes_data <- readRDS("itunes_data.rds")

apple_data  <- apple_data %>%
  mutate(trackId = as.integer(trackId))

song_data = apple_data %>%
  inner_join(itunes_data, by = "trackId")

print(song_data)

saveRDS(song_data, "song_data.rds")
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)

song_data <- readRDS("song_data.rds")

data_au <- slice(song_data, 1:100) %>%
  mutate(country = "Australia")

data_canada <- slice(song_data, 101:200) %>%
  mutate(country = "Canada")

data_mex <- slice(song_data, 201:300) %>%
  mutate(country = "Mexico")

data_us <- slice(song_data, 301:400) %>%
  mutate(country = "USA")

song_data <- rbind(data_au, data_canada)
song_data <- rbind(song_data, data_mex)
song_data <- rbind(song_data, data_us)

data <- song_data %>%
  group_by(country = country) %>%
  count(trackExplicitness)

p <- ggplot(data, aes(x = country, y = n, group = trackExplicitness, color = trackExplicitness, fill = trackExplicitness)) +
  geom_col(position = "dodge2") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("explicit" = "red", "notExplicit" = "blue")) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("explicit" = "red", "notExplicit" = "blue")) +
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "#6f8f84", color = "#6f8f84")) +
  labs(x = "Country", y = "Total Number", title = "Number of Explicit and Non Explicit Top 100 Songs Across 4 Countries", caption = "Data collected from Apple music")

ggsave("song_vis.png", width = 8, height = 5, units = "in")
library(magick)
library(tidyverse)

data <- readRDS("song_data.rds")

us_data <- slice(data, 301:400)
us_data = select(us_data, -c(1))

animation <- image_blank(color = "white", width = 300, height = 300) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "USA Top 100\nMusic Hits", size = 20, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Source: Apple Music", size = 10, gravity = "south")

for (i in 1:nrow(us_data)) {
  img <- image_blank(color = "#4287f5", width = 300, height = 300) %>%
    image_annotate(text = paste0(i, ":\n", us_data[i, ]), size = 22, gravity = "center")
  
  animation <- c(animation, img)
}

animation <- image_animate(animation, fps = 1, dispose = "previous")

image_write(animation, "animation.gif")
